tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured laboratory values are within normal limits for this patient, including renal function, electrolytes, and glucose metabolism. Hemoglobin A1c is at the upper end of normal, suggesting good but borderline glycemic control. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected. Continued monitoring is recommended.
